"title": "4440: fig-tree",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4440: fig-tree",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A tree common in the Near East, with soft, sweet fruit which can be eaten fresh or dried. The fruit was an important part of the diet in biblical times and the tree was symbolic of peace and security.</p>\n<h2>Figs</h2>\n<h3>Figs prized as a sweet, pleasant fruit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:10-Judg9:11\">JDG 9:10–9:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num13:21-Num13:23\">NUM 13:21–13:23</a></p>\n<h3>Figs a significant part of the diet in biblical times</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num20:5\">NUM 20:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:7-Deut8:9\">DEU 8:7–8:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam30:11-1Sam30:12\">1SA 30:11–30:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:15\">NEH 13:15</a></p>\n<h3>Figs given in gifts of food</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:18\">1SA 25:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam16:1\">2SA 16:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:40\">1CH 12:40</a></p>\n<h3>Other uses of figs and fig leaves</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs20:1-2Kgs20:7\">2KI 20:1–20:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:6-Gen3:7\">GEN 3:6–3:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa38:21\">ISA 38:21</a></p>\n<h3>Judah likened to figs</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer24:1-Jer24:10\">JER 24:1–24:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer29:15-Jer29:19\">JER 29:15–29:19</a></p>\n<h2>The fig-tree as a symbol of peace and security</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs4:25\">1KI 4:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:28-2Kgs18:32\">2KI 18:28–18:32</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa36:13-Isa36:18\">ISA 36:13–36:18</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:1-Mic4:5\">MIC 4:1–4:5</a></strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech3:10\">ZEC 3:10</a></p>\n<h2>Destruction of fig-trees</h2>\n<h3>By God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:12\">HOS 2:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:33\">PSA 105:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos4:9\">AMO 4:9</a></p>\n<h3>By enemies</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:6-Joel1:7\">JOL 1:6–1:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:17\">JER 5:17</a></p>\n<h2>Descriptions of the fig-tree and its fruit</h2>\n<h3>Early figs</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos9:10\">HOS 9:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song2:13\">SNG 2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa28:4\">ISA 28:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:1\">MIC 7:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah3:12\">NAM 3:12</a></p>\n<h3>Late figs</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:12-Rev6:13\">REV 6:12–6:13</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Failure of the crop</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer8:13\">JER 8:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:12\">JOL 1:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab3:17-Hab3:18\">HAB 3:17–3:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag2:19\">HAG 2:19</a></p>\n<h2>Fig-trees in the teaching of Jesus Christ and the apostles</h2>\n<h3>In parables and object lessons</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:9-Jas3:12\">JAS 3:9–3:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:15-Matt7:20\">MAT 7:15–7:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:43-Luke6:45\">LUK 6:43–6:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:6-Luke13:9\">LUK 13:6–13:9</a></p>\n<h3>The lesson of the fig-tree</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:32-Matt24:35\">MAT 24:32–24:35</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:28-Mark13:31\">MRK 13:28–13:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:29-Luke21:31\">LUK 21:29–21:31</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ curses a fig-tree</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:18-Matt21:22\">MAT 21:18–21:22</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:12-Mark11:14\">MRK 11:12–11:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:20-Mark11:24\">MRK 11:20–11:24</a></p>",
